<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium frontale" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium frontale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
derives from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">frontalis</emphasis>
(forehead) and refers to the different sculpture and colouration of this species compared with the common and widespread 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. ardens" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="comparative diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Comparative diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
We describe 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium frontale" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium frontale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" baseAuthorityName="Coquebert" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium ardens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" baseAuthorityName="Coquebert" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium ardens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Coquebert, 1801), yet some diagnostic morphological characters clearly separate it. Brow more convex above scapal basin; different sculpture, with wide, polished interspaces (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Hedychridium frontale sp. nov., female, paratype (A, C, E, F) and H. ardens (Coquebert), female (from Mongolia) (B, D) A head, frontal view C metasoma, postero-lateral view E habitus, dorsal view F habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view D metasoma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608677" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">10A</figureCitation>
) [vs. densely punctate in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. ardens" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Hedychridium frontale sp. nov., female, paratype (A, C, E, F) and H. ardens (Coquebert), female (from Mongolia) (B, D) A head, frontal view C metasoma, postero-lateral view E habitus, dorsal view F habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view D metasoma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608677" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">10B</figureCitation>
)]; scapal basin medially, finely microridged only on lower half, from mid-face to clypeus (vs. microridged area longitudinally more expanded); lateral micropunctures from mid- eye to malar space (vs. more extended); clypeal apical margin bordered by a thick brownish rim 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
MOD long (vs. not longer than 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
MOD); head concolorous green, with a bluish highlight laterally to clypeus (vs. bicolour with purplish vertex, greenish brow and blue face); mouthparts more elongate; median area of metapostnotum (median area of postnotum situated between the propodeum and T1) smaller (compare Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Hedychridium frontale sp. nov., female, paratype (A, C, E, F) and H. ardens (Coquebert), female (from Mongolia) (B, D) A head, frontal view C metasoma, postero-lateral view E habitus, dorsal view F habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view D metasoma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608677" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">10C and D</figureCitation>
); metasomal with sparser punctures (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Hedychridium frontale sp. nov., female, paratype (A, C, E, F) and H. ardens (Coquebert), female (from Mongolia) (B, D) A head, frontal view C metasoma, postero-lateral view E habitus, dorsal view F habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view D metasoma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608677" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">10C</figureCitation>
); S2 without metallic spot (vs. with metallic spot); legs black to dark purple in ventral view (vs. greenish).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
